Analyze Your Data
Salesforce Analytics Tools
Reports and Dashboards
Manage Your Reports and Dashboards on Analytics Home
Reports
Dashboards
Build a Dashboard
Create custom reports containing the data you want to display.
Click the Dashboards tab, Go To Dashboard List, and click New Dashboard.
Customize your dashboard and click Save.
A dashboard shows data from source reports as visual components.
The components provide a snapshot of key metrics and performance indicators for your organization.
To edit an existing dashboard, click its name from the list and customize.
You can clone a dashboard to quickly create a dashboard with the same properties and components.
Required Editions and User Permissions: Available in Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
User Permissions Needed:
To create dashboards: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you didnâ€™t create in public folders: Manage Dashboards in Public Folders
